:\"stdClass\":12:{s:2:\"id\";i:2676480;s:4:\"slug\";s:8:\"markdown\";s:5:\"title\";s:8:\"Markdown\";s:11:\"create_date\";s:19:\"2017-11-21 17:22:46\";s:13:\"modified_date\";s:19:\"2018-06-27 07:58:06\";s:6:\"status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:4:\"link\";s:52:\"https://www.peepso.com/?post_type=download&p=2676480\";s:7:\"content\";s:3647:\"Text formatting in Posts and Comments. End of the year is upon us. It\'d be nice to give you something before the end of the year. It\'s a plugin that we have been looking forward ourselves too. We needed a way to easily and safely format text within our own community. So that we can answer questions and provide well formatted answers at the same time.\r\n\r\nIt does make a difference especially when you have to deal with code snippets or at least put emphasis on certain parts of your post or comment. What is Markdown and why is the plugin named like that?\r\n<blockquote><em>Markdown is a lightweight markup language with plain text formatting syntax. It is designed so that it can be converted to HTML and many other formats using a tool by the same name. Markdown is often used to format readme files, for writing messages in online discussion forums, and to create rich text using a plain text editor</em>. - <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Wikipedia</a>.</blockquote>\r\nMarkdown is widely used across the web. It\'s the cornerstone of quick, simple and safe text formatting. Markdown is extremely powerful, but we have decided that in the first version we\'ll adapt just bits and pieces of it.\r\n<h2>Where Can I Use It?</h2>\r\nIt can be used in both Posts and Comments throughout PeepSo. There are settings where you can allow Markdown in Posts and / or Comments. Just go to the backend of your site: PeepSo &gt; Configuration &gt; Markdown and flip the switches. There\'s also a quick cheatsheet on available Markdown formatting.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-2814675\" src=\"https://www.peepso.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/peepso_social_networking_plugin_for_wordpress_markdown_screenshot_settings-1024x248.png\" alt=\"Markdown Configuration\" width=\"1024\" height=\"248\" />\r\n<h2>How Can I Format Text?</h2>\r\n<h3>Available Formatting</h3>\r\nThe available ways to format text are:\r\n\r\n<strong>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Duis feugiat tortor risus, vitae volutpat lacus volutpat a. Sed vitae sapien augue. Curabitur posuere nec felis eu pretium.</strong>\r\nby using: **DoubleAsterisks**\r\n\r\n<em>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Duis feugiat tortor risus, vitae volutpat lacus volutpat a. Sed vitae sapien augue. Curabitur posuere nec felis eu pretium.\r\n</em>by using: *SingleAsterisk*\r\n\r\n<del>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Duis feugiat tortor risus, vitae volutpat lacus volutpat a. Sed vitae sapien augue. Curabitur posuere nec felis eu pretium.</del>\r\nby using: ~~DoubleTilde~~\r\n\r\nThe above text formatting styles can be combined too. <strong>You can <del>do</del></strong> <em><del><strong>what</strong></del> <del>you</del> want</em>. :)\r\n<h3>Lists</h3>\r\nIt comes also with the possibility of creating ordered lists\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Milk</li>\r\n 	<li>Bread</li>\r\n 	<li>Butter</li>\r\n 	<li>Cheese</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nWhich can be created just by placing a number and a dot / full stop: 1. Milk 2. Bread 3. Butter\r\n\r\nYou can also create unordered lists\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Milk</li>\r\n 	<li>Bread</li>\r\n 	<li>Butter</li>\r\n 	<li>Cheese</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSimilarly to ordered lists you can just put a dash or an asterisk in front of a word. Like: - / *. Lists will then be created.\r\n<h3>Code</h3>\r\nYou can also include inline code by putting `<code>in front of a line of code and closing with the same symbol</code>`.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-3287727 size-full\" src=\"https://www.peepso.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/peepso_social_networking_plugin_for_wordpress_markdown_screenshot-1.png\" alt=\"Markdown formatting example\" width=\"1336\" height=\"1973\" />\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s:73:\"https://www.peepso.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/2018/03/markdown_icon-2.png\";s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":10:{s:7:\"term_id\";i:13365;s:4:\"name\";s:12:\"Integrations\";s:4:\"slug\";s:12:\"integrations\";s:10:\"term_group\";i:0;s:16:\"term_taxonomy_id\";i:13365;s:8:\"taxonomy\";s:17:\"download_category\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"parent\";i:13361;s:5:\"count\";i:4;s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}}s:4:\"tags\";a:4:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":10:{s:7:\"term_id\";i:13463;s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"formatting\";s:4:\"slug\";s:10:\"formatting\";s:10:\"term_group\";i:0;s:16:\"term_taxonomy_id\";i:13463;s:8:\"taxonomy\";s:12:\"download_tag\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"parent\";i:0;s:5:\"count\";i:1;s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":10:{s:7:\"term_id\";i:13461;s:4:\"name\";s:8:\"markdown\";s:4:\"slug\";s:8:\"markdown\";s:10:\"term_group\";i:0;s:16:\"term_taxonomy_id\";i:13461;s:8:\"taxonomy\";s:12:\"download_tag\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"parent\";i:0;s:5:\"count\";i:1;s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":10:{s:7:\"term_id\";i:13478;s:4:\"name\";s:20:\"PeepSoMarkdownPlugin\";s:4:\"slug\";s:20:\"peepsomarkdownplugin\";s:10:\"term_group\";i:0;s:16:\"term_taxonomy_id\";i:13478;s:8:\"taxonomy\";s:12:\"download_tag\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"parent\";i:0;s:5:\"count\";i:1;s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":10:{s:7:\"term_id\";i:13462;s:4:\"name\";s:15:\"text formatting\";s:4:\"slug\";s:15:\"text-formatting\";s:10:\"term_group\";i:0;s:16:\"term_taxonomy_id\";i:13462;s:8:\"taxonomy\";s:12:\"download_tag\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"parent\";i:0;s:5:\"count\";i:1;s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}}}s:7:\"pricing\";O:8:\"stdClass\":1:{s:6:\"amount\";s:5:\"29.00\";}s:9:\"licensing\";O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:7:\"enabled\";b:1;s:7:\"version\";s:6:\"1.10.3\";s:8:\"exp_unit\";s:5:\"years\";s:10:\"exp_length\";s:1:\"1\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:4:\"info\";O:8:\"stdClass\":12:{s:2:\"id\";i:2014551;s:4:\"slug\";s:21:\"cm-strava-integration\";s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"CM Strava Integration\";s:11:\"create_date\";s:19:\"2017-10-24 10:09:04\";s:13:\"modified_date\";s:19:\"2017-11-27 11:31:03\";s:6:\"status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:4:\"link\";s:52:\"https://www.peepso.com/?post_type=download&p=2014551\";s:7:\"content\";s:1438:\"Allow users to share their STRAVA routes &amp; statistics.\r\n<div class=\"cmwarning\">\r\n\r\nThis integration requires you to have a Strava account and to create a <a href=\"https://www.strava.com/settings/api\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Strava App</strong></a>.\r\n\r\nThe technical support for this Integration is provided by the <strong><a href=\"https://www.cminds.com/wordpress-plugin-customer-support-ticket/?af=7789\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">CreativeMinds</a></strong>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nThe Addon lets you attach your Strava activities right in your your posts on PeepSo Stream. User needs to connect with his Strava account from his profile. This is made for each user separately. Once user connects to Strava all his Strava activities are sharable on PeepSo stream.\r\n\r\nOnce user post his activities, for each activity there will also be a map showing the route itself and the route parameters.\r\n\r\nAdmin can also add a widget to show a user summary of all activities for a given period of time like a week and this year. The widget also shows links to a more detailed view about the latest activity. There is another widget which shows activities of a user whose profile you\'re looking at.\r\n<h3>Features include:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Share activities from Strava on Peepso stream</li>\r\n 	<li>Show user accumulated distance for this week and this month</li>\r\n 	<li>Show route from Strava on a Google Map</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[edd-screenshots]\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s